## ════════════════════════════════════════
## TYPE 2: WEB APPLICATION
## ════════════════════════════════════════

### Pipeline Order: ARCHITECTURE-FIRST

```
0 → IDEA          PRD.md locked
1 → VALIDATE      Risks + improvements confirmed
2 → RESEARCH      Market research + competitor features → MARKET_RESEARCH.md
3 → ARCHITECTURE  Data model + API design + auth + roles → ARCHITECTURE.md
4 → IA            App navigation, user flows, screen map → IA_CONTENT.md
5 → DESIGN        Design system: tokens, components, states, flows → DESIGN.md
6 → CONTENT       UI copy, empty states, error messages, onboarding → CONTENT_MAP.md
7 → SCAFFOLD      Full file tree → PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md + scaffold.sh
8 → BUILD         Feature slices (auth first, core features, extras)
9 → HARDEN        Security + perf + a11y + data integrity audit
10 → SHIP         Deploy + monitoring + error tracking live
```

**Why this order:**
- Data model must be locked before UI is designed (forms, tables, relations)
- Auth and roles defined before any screen is drawn
- IA maps user flows, not just pages — requires architecture context
- Content (UI copy) is last because it depends on knowing every screen state

### Hardlock Table (Web App)

| To enter this step | Requires                                                     | Rollback trigger (re-open this phase) |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| RESEARCH           | PRD.md locked                                                | ICP/feature set pivot before arch lock |
| arabic_seo_hardlock | IF onboarding.yaml:target_market contains "mena" OR "ar" THEN arabic-seo-aeo-specialist MUST produce docs/seo/arabic-seo-brief.md before RESEARCH phase completes | CONDITIONAL |
| ARCHITECTURE       | PRD.md + market research + PROJECT_PROMPT.md aligned         | Auth model, data model, or integration contracts change materially |
| IA                 | ARCHITECTURE.md with data model + auth model confirmed       | User roles, flows, nav, or screen map invalid vs arch |
| DESIGN             | IA_CONTENT.md with user flows + screen map                   | New major surfaces; token/component contracts break IA assumptions |
| CONTENT            | DESIGN.md — need all screens to know all copy states         | Voice, empty/error states scope changes post-design |
| SCAFFOLD           | ARCHITECTURE.md + DESIGN.md + IA_CONTENT.md all exist        | Package/tree no longer reflects arch or DESIGN |
| BUILD              | PROJECT_SCAFFOLD.md confirmed + all SDD prereqs pass         | SPEC invalid vs IA/arch; cross-slice coupling explosion |
| HARDEN             | All feature slices pass acceptance criteria                  | New risk surfaces added without hardened review |
| SHIP               | All harden audits pass                                       | Regressions in security/perf/a11y gates |

